<LIST>
<HEAD>R.</HEAD>
<ITEM><HI>Rea&s;on,</HI> or the <HI>knowledge of good and evil,</HI> was unlawfully a&s;|&s;umed by our <HI>fir&s;t parents,</HI> 11. 43. 192. Is the cau&s;e that <HI>&s;in</HI> is imputed to us, 30. A <HI>divine attribute,</HI> which the Gen|tiles acknowledged, 31, 32. Is properly the <HI>grand prin|ciple,</HI> or <HI>law of nature,</HI> or <HI>con&s;cience,</HI> 37. Man not en|dowed with &s;o ample a portion of it <HI>before the fall,</HI> 41, et &s;eq. A <HI>rule of obedience,</HI> 33. God <HI>requires us</HI> to exert it, 89. See <HI>Knowledge of Good and Evil, Sindere&s;is, Con|&s;cience.</HI></ITEM>
